docs.abstract: If Apple chooses to settle its lawsuit against Qualcomm, it could preserve the company’s independence from Broadcom.
docs.snippet: If Apple chooses to settle its lawsuit against Qualcomm, it could preserve the company’s independence from Broadcom.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple may anoint the winner of Broadcom’s $105 billion bid for Qualcomm. A dispute over iPhone royalties left Qualcomm vulnerable to an opportunistic offer from its acquisitive rival. If Apple settles its dispute, it could preserve Qualcomm’s independence — but it all depends on whether Apple thinks a bigger Broadcom would be slavishly devoted to its devices, or just surlier.

headline.main: Will Qualcomm Agree to a Deal With Broadcom? Ask Apple
